\begin{equation}
    \frac{d^2Q}{dt^2} + 2\gamma \frac{dQ}{dt} + \omega_0^2 Q = 0
\end{equation}

where $\gamma$ and $\omega_0^2$ are to be determined in terms of the capacitance $C$, inductance $L$, and resistance $R$.

For a resistance $R = 100 \, \Omega$, capacitance $C = 700 \, \text{pF}$, and inductance $L = 80 \, \text{mH}$, calculate:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item[(a)] The natural frequency, $f_0$, of the oscillation.
    \item[(b)] The time constant, $\tau$, for the decay.
\end{enumerate}

