The differential equation for an RLC circuit is given by:

\begin{equation}
    L \frac{d^2Q}{dt^2} + R \frac{dQ}{dt} + \frac{Q}{C} = 0
\end{equation}

Comparing this with the standard form:

\begin{equation}
    \frac{d^2Q}{dt^2} + 2\gamma \frac{dQ}{dt} + \omega_0^2 Q = 0
\end{equation}

we identify:

\begin{align*}
    2\gamma &= \frac{R}{L} \\
    \omega_0^2 &= \frac{1}{LC}
\end{align*}

